This program is just to show, how we can pass parameters to a Linux kernel
module.

Just define a global variable and then make it as a module parameter with the
use of 'module_param' function.

For example,

static int num = 5;
module_param(num, int, 0660);

static char *str = "string arg";
module_param(str, charp, 0660);

Then, We can use these variables inside any other functions of this Linux kernel
module.

[ ] make
[ ] sudo insmod mymodule.ko
[ ] lsmod | grep mymodule
mymodule               16384  0
[ ] dmesg | tail
[ 5864.593807] Hello, Linux Kernel. num = 5, str = string arg
[ ] sudo rmmod mymodule
[ ] dmesg | tail
[ 5885.700191] Bye, Linux Kernel. num = 5, str = string arg
